Doctor: Patient reports seasonal allergy symptoms—sneezing, itchy eyes, and nasal congestion.
    Starting loratadine 10mg once daily during allergy season. Recommend using a HEPA air purifier
    at home and avoiding outdoor activities during high pollen count days. Schedule an allergy test
    panel in 3 weeks. Nurse: I’ll arrange the test appointment and send pollen tracking resources
    to the patient portal.

Doctor: Patient is in her first trimester of pregnancy. Recommending daily prenatal vitamin with folic acid, 
    and iron supplement 325mg once daily. Advise on avoiding high-mercury fish and limiting caffeine intake. 
    Schedule ultrasound in 4 weeks and routine prenatal labs. Patient should report any bleeding or severe cramps immediately.
    Nurse: I'll set up the ultrasound and labs.

    I’m prescribing albuterol nebulizer treatments every 4 hours as needed, and starting fluticasone 
    44mcg two puffs twice daily for maintenance. Parent should track symptoms using an asthma diary.
